Rating: 3
Made this again last night for the first time in about a year. Still great. Still shows well for dinner guests (which mine was for a client). Learned a few new adjustments that I'll be making on my go rounds: Yes to White Wine vinegar instead of Cider however either the quantity need be reduced or you need to reduce the liquid for much more time than recommended (I reduced 1 1/2 tbls in the wine for about 15 mins). I added salt and pepper to the end broth, which is not on the recipe but very effective. Also, I used Rainbow Chard and found that to be a more complex and crisper leaf for this dish. I imagine that leafy kale or any other chard would do well. I also think that the next time I make this I'm going to add a bit more mustard for a richer texture (I used whole grain). Though I used Marlborough Sav Blanc, I'm not sure it was necessary to use that specific of a dry white.

