I found this to be a rather enjoyable and easy way to flavor and present salmon. My changes: Purple potatoes, 1 Tbl garlic to the leafy saute for a minute, roasted corn to the broth added pre bake, a few tablespoons of brothy/ starchy water added to the broth (leftover from reconstituted dried garbonzos used to make roasted garlic hummus days before) and a little less vinegar than called for. Not so likely that I'll have "garbonzo water" on hand when I next make this but, hey, I also used an exceptional mustard (Maille- gifted to me straight from Paris) so maybe THAT was the secret to the sauce! Now I'll soap box: It's weird to me that anyone would make a daily meal "by the book" and be disappointed with the results. I believe that recipes are guides not rulebooks. I have fun with them (who has exact ingredients all the time and flavor-experimenting is a blast), taste along the way and adjust as necessary. I'm only precise when baking or when trying to pull off something really special, which is when I'm neurotic in the kitchen.

