This recipe turned out great the first time. I picked up good quality wild salmon and sliced the skin off myself. Searing both sides is key. I also cooked the broth in advance and let sit. The potatoes however took much longer to cook. I boiled new red potatoes for 15 minutes before baking with the salmon. When I pulled the dish after about 18 min (I wanted to ensure salmon didn't overcook) the potatoes were still far from cooked through. So I pulled the salmon and put it the fillets on a plate keeping warm, then added some more broth and baked the potatoes for another 15 min. Then I turned the oven off and put the salmon back in to warm up before serving over the wilted spinach. Next time I'll just boil the potatoes for another 10-15 min.

